<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL
        (Removal and Reassembly) - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil seal in (new or original) rear cover as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>IF THE OPTIONAL REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE PACKAGE (PART NO. 1 807 788 C92) IS USED, THE
                        NEW "OVERSIZE" REAR OIL SEAL (INCLUDED IN THE PACKAGE) MUST BE INSTALLED. FOLLOW THE
                        INSTRUCTIONS INCLUDED IN THE PACKAGE.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position seal protector tool
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE1942-2A</emph>, onto installer tool
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4131</emph>
                    (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350622">6.22</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lubricate seal lip with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Press seal positioned as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350623">6.23</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    over protector until it stops against installer tool. Remove protector from installer tool.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350622" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11103" filename="../figcg1/CG11103.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.22</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350623" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10647" filename="../figcg1/CG10647.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.23</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place 3, 1 inch high x 2 inch long x 5/8 inch wide metal blocks (made locally) on the
                    bed of an arbor press, arranged as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_109.xml" xrefid="ef4350624">6.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coat seal bore I.D. in rear cover with a thin coat of Aviation Permatext #3, as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_109.xml" xrefid="ef4350625">6.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place rear cover over blocks as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_109.xml" xrefid="ef4350626">6.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    with press ram on installing tool. Press oil seal into rear cover bore until tool bottoms on plate.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
